  "prompt": "My boyfriend cheated on me. I felt betrayed and it still haunts me. How to stop thinking about it?",
  "response": "Dealing with betrayal can be challenging. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Emotional Processing\n- Allow yourself to feel your emotions\n- Consider talking to a therapist\n- Journal your feelings\n- Practice self-compassion\n\n2. Relationship Decisions\n- Decide if you want to work on the relationship or leave\n- If staying, consider couples counseling\n- If leaving, create a support system\n\n3. Personal Healing\n- Focus on self-care\n- Engage in activities you enjoy\n- Exercise and maintain healthy habits\n- Spend time with supportive friends/family\n\n4. Mental Strategies\n- Practice mindfulness meditation\n- Challenge negative thought patterns\n- Avoid obsessive rumination\n- Set boundaries with your partner\n\n5. Professional Help\n- Individual counseling can provide coping strategies\n- Therapy can help process trauma and rebuild self-esteem\n\n6. Future Prevention\n- Learn from the experience\n- Establish clear relationship expectations\n- Build trust gradually\n- Work on communication skills\n\nRemember healing takes time. Be patient with yourself and prioritize your mental and emotional well-being.\n\nWould you like to discuss any specific aspect of your situation?",
